solution: ```class Solution {
    public int appendCharacters(String s, String t) {
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        int m = s.length(), n = t.length();
        while (i < m && j < n) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j)) {
                j++;
            }
            i++;
        }
        return n - j;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(m + n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Two-pointer greedy scan: advance through s while matching t in order; the remaining unmatched suffix of t is exactly what must be appended. Single pass, constant memory, optimal.

